This paper deals with the security of wireless communication systems, which is a common topic in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on the scheduling of friendly jammers, which is related to the design and optimization of wireless networks, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which are common in the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of energy consumption and network lifetime, which is related to the control and optimization of dynamical systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category as well.
